Foremost
File carving tool

Forensics
Description
Foremost is a console program to recover files based on their headers, footers, and internal data structures (file carving).

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which foremost
Install command:

sudo apt install foremost
Basic Syntax
foremost -i <input> -o <output>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
foremost -i disk.img -o output/

Carve all files	Recover deleted files	
foremost -t jpg -i disk.img -o output/

JPG only	Specific file type	
foremost -t pdf,doc -i disk.img -o output/

Multiple types	Documents only	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Obtain disk image
2
Run foremost
3
Check output directory
4
Review recovered files
5
Document findings
Understanding the Output
Creates directories with recovered files organized by type.

Important Warnings
•
Works on copies only
•
May recover partial files
•
Output can be large
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
